The mystery surrounding the untimely death of Zindzi Mandela has been solved. Zindzi ‘s son, Zondwa ,has announced that his mother tested positive for COVID-19. Zindzi, who served as South Africa’s Ambassador to Denmark, died on Monday at a Johannesburg hospital. Zondwa announced the news on SABC on Wednesday evening. He said Zindzi, whose autopsy results were still outstanding, will be buried this coming Friday. Ngwako Malatji